data.name: HelpCube_Text
data.value: Rotate the cube sides 'clockwise' and 'counter clockwise': If the command is given to turn the front 'clockwise' then this is in the direction the hands are turning. 'Counter clockwise' is turning in the other direction. For the other sides you always have to 'imagine' that you are directly in front of the side to be turned. So if it says turn the back 'clockwise' imagine you are on the other side of the cube and then turn the back 'clockwise'. Do not rotate the cube itself.

You can always contact me for any corrections.

data.name: HelpOptionsSolveCube_Text
data.value: Options to solve the cube: 1. On the home screen, use the arrow keys to mix up the cube and solve the cube with the arrow keys. 2. Same as the first option, but solve the cube with the 'Solve' button. The cube is then solved in reverse order. 3. Use the button with the cube at the bottom of the screen to transfer the colors of your cube to this cube (see the explanation of that button). The cube will be solved by the application. Then transfer the proposed moves to the real cube. This is not a guarantee that all cubes can be solved.
